      "message": "[Critical] Line 374: 🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge: Normal REMB feedback no longer increases bitrate. `onRembFeedback(false)` only moves `Draining -\u003e Probing`, and later normal REMB packets do nothing because `state_ \u003d\u003d State::Draining` is false. This regresses the old `delayProcessing(0x7378)` behavior and contradicts the comment saying recovery works even without RR. Apply an increase when normal REMB is received in `Probing`.\n\n```suggestion\n    if (!isOveruse) {\n        auto secSinceDecrease \u003d secSinceLastDecrease(now);\n        if (state_ \u003d\u003d State::Draining \u0026\u0026 secSinceDecrease \u003e cfg_.probeDelaySec) {\n            state_ \u003d State::Probing;\n            JAMI_LOG(\"[BandwidthCtrl] REMB normal -\u003e entering PROBING state\");\n        }\n        if (state_ \u003d\u003d State::Probing)\n            applyIncrease();\n    }\n```",
