      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 873: 🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider: `lastRembSent_` rate-limits both normal and overuse REMB packets. A normal/increase REMB can therefore suppress an urgent overuse REMB for up to 500 ms, delaying congestion reaction compared with the previous independent decrease limiter. Use separate timestamps or always prioritize overuse feedback.\n\n```suggestion\n        if (bwState \u003d\u003d BandwidthUsage::bwOverusing) {\n            if (now - lastRembOveruseSent_ \u003e\u003d MIN_REMB_INTERVAL) {\n                rembPacket \u003d cc-\u003ecreateREMB(0x6803);\n                lastRembOveruseSent_ \u003d now;\n            }\n        } else if (bwState \u003d\u003d BandwidthUsage::bwNormal) {\n            if (now - lastRembNormalSent_ \u003e\u003d std::chrono::seconds(1)) {\n                rembPacket \u003d cc-\u003ecreateREMB(0x7378);\n                lastRembNormalSent_ \u003d now;\n            }\n        }\n```",
