      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 887: 🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge: `socketPair_` is checked while holding `mutex_`, but dereferenced after the lock is released. Because `socketPair_` is a `unique_ptr` that can be reset by another media/control thread, this introduces a use-after-free/data race in the RTP delay callback. Keep the dereference synchronized, or change ownership so the callback can hold a safe reference.\n\n```suggestion\n    if (!rembPacket.empty()) {\n        std::lock_guard lock(mutex_);\n        if (socketPair_)\n            socketPair_-\u003ewriteData(rembPacket.data(), static_cast\u003cint\u003e(rembPacket.size()));\n    }\n```",
